
Python scripts to help create input images to LIRA. All scripts 
require CIAO4.5 including contrib scripts -  http://cxc.harvard.edu/ciao/

Simulation script requires Sherpa for image fitting part:
http://cxc.harvard.edu/sherpa/



rebin_img.py  - a function to make an image with the center pixel 
	       located at the region centroid
make_img.py   - example script showing the usage of rebin_img.py
rebin_psf.py  - a function to rebin psf file to match the binning and the centroid
	      of the image.
sim_image.py  - simulations to generate images of the data based on the null model
	      
